features: Made in USA: Manufactured under the highest standards in the USA in NSF GMP Certified facility and third party lab verified for purity, potency, and quality. MaxMight Iron Complex is free of GMOs, gluten, dairy, soy, wheat, eggs, fish, shellfish, peanuts, tree nuts, sugar, artificial additives and preservatives.

Highly-Absorbed Energy Formula*: Pumping iron at the gym requires pumping up your iron stores as well. We offer 36 mg of readily-available iron in the form of ferrous bisglycinate chelate to give you the best possible nutrition with less stress on your stomach.* Maxmight’s innovative formula is also enhanced with activated B vitamins & Vitamin C to bump up your energy for peak performance in every workout!*

B Your Most Energetic Self*: Besides high-strength iron that supports oxygen-rich blood for working muscles, we also fuel your body with 3 methylated B vitamins to help you hit the gym with increased stamina & muscle strength.* Our iron complex also helps buffer fatigue for better mental focus & clarity during & after workout.* Whether you need a total pre-workout prep or just temporary afternoon boost, only 1 easy-to-swallow capsule a day can help you go the distance.*

MaxMight Life, Starts Here: Decades of diligent research and an unwavering commitment to wellness goes Into every bottle. Whether you're a seasoned athlete or just starting out, we have you covered with the supplements you need to fuel your passion and achieve your goals.

Celebrate Your MaxMight Potential: MaxMight Iron Complex is a product of 30 years of scientific research, development and testing. We are devoted to deliver quality nutritional formulations that nourish and restore optimal health & vitality and encourage everyone to commit themselves fully to their active lifestyles and achieve their MaxMight potential.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 1, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Excellent Source of Iron!!!
reviews.reviewText: This order came with (I think) 60 iron capsules.So, these are perfect, especially for someone with a deficiency of iron, like myself. I’ve been searching for a good source of iron lately, as I am anemic. The truth is, I don’t actually know exactly how much iron I get from food or other sources, and I should probably start with knowing that, but I honestly can’t imagine that it’s TOO much. These are small, easy to swallow, and taste like metal. I like all of those things. Highly recommend.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 14, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Good iron supplement
reviews.reviewText: It's an easy pill to get more iron. I seem to have an iron deficiency and taking these does help my iron levels and helps me out. They are easy to take and I have one each morning.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 23, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Easily Absorbed with No Stomach Discomfort!
reviews.reviewText: My wife and I both take these for low iron. These are excellent quality and have a good dosage of 36mg of iron per capsule. The bottle contains a generous amount of 60 servings. In addition, these have some great supportive ingredients in good dosages. We find the bisglycinate form of iron to be gentle and easily absorbed. Although we haven't had lab work to confirm this, I am confident our iron levels have improved from our increased energy and general feeling of well-being. The capsules are easy to swallow with no bad taste or odor and cause no stomach discomfort. We take one per day with meals as suggested. These are a great price for the quality, ingredients, and amount.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 25, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars These seem to work as well for me as the other iron supplements I have taken in the past
reviews.reviewText: Dietary and nutritional supplements do not receive the same regulation as prescription or over-the-counter drugs. Like all consumers, I don't have a lab to check for harmful levels of contaminants and if the supplements contain the ingredients listed on the label and nothing else, so we have to take their word for it. That said, these are easy to swallow and seem to work as well for me as the other iron supplements I have taken in the past. I also like that these are made in the USA.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 18, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Daily Iron for Growth and Recovery
reviews.reviewText: I've never specifically supplemented iron, but I have heard a lot about the natural benefits of including it in your workout nutritional intake. This product seems like a good intro with one daily pill that I included into my morning pills. I actually didn't think much of it, but after a week, I noticed a greater recovery and bounce back from my daily gym workouts! Could be placebo and all in my head, could be not, but so far it does seem to work! Give it a shot.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 11, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars They added other ingredients to prevent digestion system discomfort
reviews.reviewText: This iron supplement works pretty well. It comes with 60 capsules, which is 2 month worth of supply if you take one per day. They also added other ingredients to prevent digestion system discomfort, which is a welcome feature for me. The size of the capsule is normal, so it's effortless to swallow and it's preferred to take after a meal.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 17, 2024
reviews.reviewText: These capsules contain 36mg of iron which is 200% of the recommended daily value (DV). They also contain 30mg vitamin C (33% DV), 5mg B6 (294% DV), 667mcg Folate (167% DV) and 30mcg B12 (1250% DV). I am taking it to increase the oxygen in my blood in an attempt to reduce hair loss caused by prescription medication. I’ve noticed less hair falling out since I began taking it. So far I am quite pleased.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 10, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Excellent supplement for synthetic iron
reviews.reviewText: Overall, this is a great supplement if you are just looking for a bioavailable iron that has other vitamins with it to help you absorb it. The amount of iron is ideal. As someone who has always struggled with iron deficiency, I realize it takes more than just your typical 18 mg of iron to increase your hemoglobin levels. I really appreciate the higher level on these. The bottle is small too, which is handy when one has a lot of other vitamin bottles in their cabinet. It is a good buy!
